      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNITZALATTE (1) comes here fresh without a trial, but brings in strong form through some key 3YO features last time in work. She progressed through the grades nicely, jumping favourite ahead of Guineas winner King Of Light in the Belgravia. Should get every chance from the inside draw and looks the one to beat. SWINGMAN (2) won well two back before just missing here over 1200m most recently in this grade. He'll enjoy it if the rain comes, with the claim of ZJP a big tick. May need some luck from the draw but his recent form shows he's good enough. KINGS COURT (3) led and won over this trip fresh before disappointing at this track and trip in a CL5 last time out. He can tend to dip second-up however so that's not a worry. His fresh run said he was back better than ever and he can return to that form today. SLIP THE JAB (5) will find this tougher, but his figures suggest he's not out of this. HURRICANE HARLEY (6) showed promise last time in work and won't be far away fresh.",
